==English==
===Noun===
'''vanilla''' (v&#601; nil' &#601;) (uncountable and countable)

#any tropical, climbing [[w:orchid|orchid]] of the genus '''''Vanilla''''' (especially '''''[[w:Vanilla planifolia|V. planifolia]]'''''), bearing podlike fruit yielding an extract used in flavoring food or in perfumes.
#the fruit or bean of this orchid, '''vanilla bean'''.
#the extract of this fruit, '''vanilla extract'''.
#a distinctive fragrant flavor characteristic of vanilla extract.
#:''You can tell that the secret [[ingredient]] missing from New Coke (registered TM) was vanilla, because certain South American economies collapsed when it was introduced, and miraculously revived when the old formula was used again.''
#any artificially produced homologue of vanilla extract, generally that produced from coal tar, '''[[w:imitation vanilla|imitation vanilla]]'''.

===Adjective===
'''vanilla'''

#pertaining to, derived from, or resembling vanilla or [[w:vanillin|vanillin]]; as, ''vanilla [[w:ice cream|ice cream]]''.
#the standard, plain, default, or unmodified variety, from association with vanilla ice cream; as, ''vanilla sex''.

